Field Detail

flag

protected boolean flag
The use of flag purely serves engineering purposes. In decomposition, some EPs are needed to be removed after a copy construction. But it's not easy to trace these EPs by any sort of equals() methods. So a flag is set to mark these to-be-removed EPs.

getAllARGvalue

public java.util.HashSet<java.lang.String> getAllARGvalue()
return all "ARG*" values in this EP. for instance, an EP looks like: 
 [ _like_v_1_rel<5:10>
 LBL: h8
 ARG0: e9
 ARG1: x6
 ARG2: x10
 ]
then it returns a list containing "e9", "x6" and "x10"

Returns:
a HashSet containing all "ARG*" values
